servings: 2
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the potato on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. Once cooked, remove from the heat and set aside to cool.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80} and chop into thirds. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and season with @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} and stir fry until browned and tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pop in a large #bowl{} and set aside. Pop your pan back on medium high heat.

Add the @sesame seeds{15} to the frying pan (no oil). Once hot, cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop them in a small bowl (don't wash the pan). Add the @miso paste{15}, @mayonnaise{1}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, @water{1} and half the @soy sauce{25} to the bowl with the sesame seeds. Mix together until well combined. Set aside.

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season both sides of the @British chicken thighs{3} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix the remaining soy sauce, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and half the lime zest in a small bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken thighs and fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins. Spoon the soy sauce and sugar mixture over the chicken in the pan for the last 2 mins of cooking.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove to a #board{} to rest for a couple of mins.

Add the roasted sweet potato to the bowl with the green beans and add the dressing. Toss to coat. Thinly slice the chicken. Add the @pea shoots{40} and chicken to the veg and toss again. Serve the salad in #bowls{}, sprinkle over the remaining lime zest. Enjoy!